  "description": [
    "Airman directs choir Britton combining Air Force career with music hobby A lifetime of music combined with an Air Force career one a vocation the other an avoca tion and with both filling an important need in our country to day Master sergeant Elton M Brit ton serving in the air defense much of his free time to work ing with chapel choirs finds both of his jobs extremely satis fying Britton began his musical life at age five by taking piano les sons and 12 years later began his Air Force career by joining the Navy Four years later In 1949 he joined the twoyearold United States Air Force While in the Navy Britton taught himself to play the organ and became interested in func tions of the chapel At Keesler AFB he continued this interest by becoming ac compianist for the Keesler mix ed chorus in their presentation of Elijah Also at Keesler he found an other interest when he met Miss Hilda J Smith of Pascagoula Miss Smith is now Mrs Britton and they have two sons Ronald and Michael Brittons next tonr oi auiy iook them to France where he became accompianist lor the Dreax AFB"
